WEBVTT

00:00.203 --> 00:02.210
<i>Male announcer:
Previously on "Bates Motel"...</i>

00:02.383 --> 00:03.882
- Yes?
- I'm Emma's mother.

00:04.422 --> 00:05.373
She came here, but now Emma

00:05.398 --> 00:06.583
hasn't heard from her since,

00:06.608 --> 00:07.968
and her phone's been disconnected.

00:08.042 --> 00:10.581
[both grunting]

00:10.582 --> 00:11.791
Rebecca Hamilton?

00:11.792 --> 00:13.641
- Yes?
- DEA.

00:13.742 --> 00:15.828
I don't want to lose you, Dr. Edwards,

00:15.875 --> 00:17.751
but don't you think that it's possible

00:17.752 --> 00:19.551
that I might make even more progress

00:19.715 --> 00:21.924
if I'm near the person
who makes me feel complete?

00:21.949 --> 00:24.131
We're going to start with
three sessions a week.

00:24.156 --> 00:25.490
I'll sign your release.

00:25.515 --> 00:27.092
<i>Certain things can never change,</i>

00:27.117 --> 00:30.251
but I will always remember that
you helped my mother at a time

00:30.252 --> 00:31.921
that she was so confused.

00:31.922 --> 00:35.621
I love him, and you
have to deal with it!

00:35.622 --> 00:37.621
Don't you think she deserves
to have a man in her life?

00:37.622 --> 00:40.292
[groans] Agh! I hate you!

00:41.475 --> 00:42.516
Norman?

00:42.541 --> 00:44.251
I'm not leaving this house tonight.

00:44.252 --> 00:46.332
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

00:51.180 --> 00:53.719
[birds chirping]

00:53.744 --> 00:56.703
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:58.000 --> 01:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:24.783 --> 01:26.047
You made coffee... I was on my way

01:26.072 --> 01:27.133
- to do that for you right now.
- Yeah.

01:27.158 --> 01:28.881
Yeah. Made a pot a while ago.

01:29.105 --> 01:30.985
It should still be
good, if you want one.

01:32.024 --> 01:33.922
- You sleep okay?
- Mm-mm. Not much.

01:37.847 --> 01:39.722
Alex, that was the hardest part.

01:40.367 --> 01:41.565
Things will be better now.

01:44.728 --> 01:45.461
How so?

01:45.634 --> 01:46.846
Because that was the first time

01:46.871 --> 01:48.671
the three of us were under
the same roof together.

01:48.672 --> 01:50.687
It was bound to be hard for Norman.

01:50.932 --> 01:52.581
Okay? But we're through
it. We're through it.

01:52.582 --> 01:53.621
We ripped off the Band-Aid.

01:53.622 --> 01:54.686
It's gonna be better now.

01:54.711 --> 01:56.339
But having him here is not the solution.

01:56.364 --> 01:58.251
He should be back at Pineview.

01:58.252 --> 01:59.637
He's going back to Pineview.

01:59.662 --> 02:00.758
I'm gonna take him to therapy today.

02:00.783 --> 02:02.300
That's not the same, and you know that.

02:02.325 --> 02:03.688
I don't know that. I'm not a doctor,

02:03.713 --> 02:05.462
and neither are you, so
you don't know that either.

02:05.487 --> 02:06.786
I'm... I'm never gonna
be that guy who just

02:06.811 --> 02:07.888
tells you what you want to hear, okay?

02:07.913 --> 02:10.042
And I don't want you to be that guy.

02:13.672 --> 02:15.381
I don't feel safe leaving
you alone with him.

02:15.382 --> 02:16.581
- That's ridiculous.
- I don't think it is.

02:16.582 --> 02:18.621
No. That is so ridiculous.

02:18.622 --> 02:20.057
You are overreacting.

02:20.277 --> 02:21.501
What if I'm not?

02:24.082 --> 02:26.211
It's just... no one
knows Norman like I do.

02:26.212 --> 02:28.961
We... we are two parts
of the same person.

02:28.962 --> 02:31.581
There's no possible way he could ever,

02:31.582 --> 02:33.881
ever in any way hurt me, ever.

02:34.298 --> 02:36.501
He... you're just so wrong.

02:40.462 --> 02:42.061
I really hope I am.

02:43.282 --> 02:44.321
[door opening]

02:56.948 --> 02:58.382
[swallows, sighs]

02:59.703 --> 03:03.019
[inhales deeply]

03:03.122 --> 03:05.081
No, no, I've got to get to work.

03:05.082 --> 03:06.767
You're not gonna take
a shower or anything?

03:06.960 --> 03:08.897
No, I'll do it at home, okay?

03:08.951 --> 03:10.067
Can we talk later?

03:10.382 --> 03:11.751
Okay.

03:31.265 --> 03:33.541
- Norma, I'll see you later.
- Okay. Yeah.

03:33.542 --> 03:36.581
<i>[dark music]</i>

03:44.367 --> 03:45.855
Alex slept on the couch.

03:46.332 --> 03:47.691
Oh, it's fine.

03:48.340 --> 03:49.458
You should go upstairs and get dressed

03:49.483 --> 03:50.581
or we'll be late for therapy.

03:50.582 --> 03:52.559
Okay, honey. Okay.

03:53.043 --> 03:54.331
I'll go get ready.

04:07.422 --> 04:10.422
[crackling electricity]

04:36.780 --> 04:38.751
Do you want to put up the
Christmas lights later?

04:38.752 --> 04:40.921
I waited for you to do that.

04:41.264 --> 04:43.244
I know you have very strong feelings

04:43.269 --> 04:44.519
about Christmas lights.

04:46.849 --> 04:47.881
Okay. Yes.

04:47.906 --> 04:49.656
Then, uh, sure, we can do that.

04:51.693 --> 04:53.773
Maybe we could ask Alex to help.

04:57.676 --> 04:59.216
You're joking.

05:00.436 --> 05:01.677
[sighs] Okay.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.945
I know last night did not go well,

05:03.946 --> 05:05.826
but we can't get caught up in that.

05:07.585 --> 05:09.026
And I believe in you. I believe in Alex,

05:09.051 --> 05:10.250
and I know this can work.

05:10.605 --> 05:11.880
It's...

05:11.881 --> 05:14.340
I mean, it's gonna feel
shitty for a little while,

05:14.341 --> 05:16.052
but we can get through it, right?

05:16.077 --> 05:17.407
We can live through it.

05:19.647 --> 05:21.268
You know, just think of Alex as someone

05:21.293 --> 05:24.293
you could share the burden
of your crazy mother.

05:31.717 --> 05:33.396
My mother, she barely knows this man,

05:33.421 --> 05:35.001
and then she just ups and marries him.

05:36.678 --> 05:37.857
That's so like her.

05:40.324 --> 05:43.457
Oh, and I found out that she
married him for the insurance...

05:44.355 --> 05:46.312
to pay for all of
this. Did you know that?

05:46.337 --> 05:48.297
That he was paying?

05:49.723 --> 05:51.340
No, I didn't know that.

05:51.833 --> 05:54.407
Hm, well, it is not
exactly normal, is it,

05:54.432 --> 05:56.251
to marry someone for their insurance?

05:58.393 --> 06:00.816
Well, perhaps she felt like
she had no other choice.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.130
Uh, no.

06:02.446 --> 06:04.171
No, I don't think that is it.

06:05.540 --> 06:07.250
What is it, then?

06:07.251 --> 06:09.790
That the marriage is, uh... is real!

06:09.791 --> 06:12.210
"Oh, hello, here's your new dad.

06:12.312 --> 06:13.352
"Oh, look at the sheriff.

06:13.377 --> 06:16.056
Here we all are together,
one big, happy family."

06:18.241 --> 06:19.724
Would that be so bad?

06:19.749 --> 06:21.741
Yes, it would, because it is not real.

06:22.047 --> 06:23.927
It is all about her fear of being alone.

06:25.758 --> 06:29.183
And so when I went
away and she was alone,

06:29.208 --> 06:31.091
the Sheriff... whoo, old Alex,

06:31.116 --> 06:33.066
he had no problem stepping in.

06:33.492 --> 06:34.821
I've always had this feeling

06:34.846 --> 06:36.302
that he's hated me, and now I know why.

06:36.327 --> 06:37.386
He wanted to be with her.

06:37.411 --> 06:40.346
Oh, he couldn't wait for
me to be locked up in here

06:40.371 --> 06:42.473
and pay for it so he
could just get to her.

06:43.778 --> 06:45.556
Oh, let me tell you, though.
He has got a big surprise

06:45.581 --> 06:48.487
coming when he realizes
just how difficult she can be

06:48.512 --> 06:51.262
and how damaged she really is!

06:53.344 --> 06:56.343
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:12.294 --> 07:13.616
Everyone sees this part of her

07:13.641 --> 07:17.231
that is normal and friendly and happy.

07:18.428 --> 07:20.217
But I see what is really there.

07:22.912 --> 07:27.040
That she is as frightened and tiny

07:27.065 --> 07:28.906
and fragile inside as a baby bird...

07:30.890 --> 07:32.269
And that she's lived
her whole life that way

07:32.294 --> 07:34.626
because she can just be
crushed by disappointment.

07:36.900 --> 07:38.989
Oh, but she doesn't let
anyone else see that but me.

07:43.240 --> 07:45.149
He's got no idea what
he's got coming for him.

07:48.070 --> 07:49.261
What'll happen next is

07:49.286 --> 07:50.926
that he won't measure
up to her standards.

07:52.400 --> 07:54.439
She'll start to pass judgment on him.

07:54.440 --> 07:56.399
Not like this or that.

07:56.400 --> 07:57.584
She'll criticize him.

07:59.440 --> 08:01.068
And after a while, he'll leave.

08:01.951 --> 08:03.279
He'll run away. He'll be gone.

08:03.280 --> 08:05.069
Her heart will be
broken, and then it'll be

08:05.070 --> 08:07.239
little old me picking up
all the broken pieces...

08:09.372 --> 08:10.701
If I can.

08:23.036 --> 08:24.075
[phone beeps]

08:24.100 --> 08:26.721
<i>[line trilling]</i>

08:26.746 --> 08:29.995
[cell phone buzzing]

08:30.020 --> 08:31.479
Hi. You okay?

08:31.480 --> 08:32.809
<i>Hi. Yeah.</i>

08:34.307 --> 08:36.041
Alex, please,

08:36.066 --> 08:38.355
he's... he's trying really, really hard.

08:38.380 --> 08:40.958
It's gonna be fine. I promise.

08:42.073 --> 08:45.309
Yeah... the important goal
here is to get him better,

08:45.310 --> 08:49.038
and having him home right now,
it might seem right short-term,

08:49.063 --> 08:50.031
but it's just... it's...

08:50.056 --> 08:51.392
<i>it's not what's best for him.</i>

08:51.417 --> 08:52.462
You don't know that.

08:52.487 --> 08:54.299
Okay, ask the doctor
what he thinks is best.

08:59.020 --> 09:00.627
Five minutes of marriage
doesn't give you the right

09:00.652 --> 09:02.213
to make decisions about my son.

09:03.756 --> 09:05.665
I... I'm not trying to do
that, and you know that.

09:05.690 --> 09:07.216
I'm... I'm... I'm shining
a light on the truth,

09:07.241 --> 09:08.570
whether you want to see it or not.

09:08.595 --> 09:10.094
I hear the judgment in your voice.

09:10.119 --> 09:12.582
You're not giving him a
chance, and it hurts me.

09:12.982 --> 09:14.611
I... I'm not trying to hurt you.

09:14.940 --> 09:16.599
<i>Well, it just makes
me feel like you...</i>

09:16.600 --> 09:18.385
you don't want to make
room for him or something.

09:18.410 --> 09:19.949
No... that's ludicrous.

09:20.049 --> 09:22.143
- Is it? <i>
- Yes, yes, it is.</i>

09:23.270 --> 09:26.769
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

09:26.770 --> 09:28.571
Yeah. I... I got to go.

09:28.683 --> 09:30.352
Okay? He's... he's
out. I got to go. Bye.

09:38.051 --> 09:39.408
Hey, let me get that. Here.

09:39.455 --> 09:41.301
It's full of scarves and hats, see?

09:41.471 --> 09:42.890
Not gonna break.

09:43.035 --> 09:45.608
But I left the boxes of books upstairs.

09:47.228 --> 09:48.599
Will you give this back to Norma?

09:48.600 --> 09:50.809
I borrowed it, and she
left this in the pocket.

09:50.906 --> 09:52.430
She's probably been missing it.

09:53.113 --> 09:54.943
- Yeah, no problem.
- Thank you.

09:58.480 --> 10:01.439
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:16.810 --> 10:18.439
What is it, Mother?

10:18.798 --> 10:20.548
What happened?

10:21.101 --> 10:22.481
Nothing.

10:25.071 --> 10:26.407
I feel like this is all my fault

10:26.440 --> 10:28.356
and I've ruined everything.

10:28.381 --> 10:31.269
No, honey, no... no.

10:31.408 --> 10:32.599
You are my whole life.

10:32.600 --> 10:33.940
You always have been.

10:35.989 --> 10:38.495
Other people are just gonna
have to understand that.

10:38.816 --> 10:40.566
You are my son.

10:43.990 --> 10:47.584
I am your son, and I always will be.

10:48.447 --> 10:49.447
Yeah.

11:03.364 --> 11:05.939
Oh, thank you.

11:05.940 --> 11:07.597
My client has considered your offer

11:07.622 --> 11:08.698
and is willing to cooperate,

11:08.723 --> 11:10.035
depending on the terms, of course,

11:10.060 --> 11:12.189
but let's clarify our deal first.

11:12.277 --> 11:13.769
We'll give you Bob Paris's murderer

11:13.770 --> 11:16.245
in exchange for no jail
time, probation only.

11:16.548 --> 11:18.559
Not if she's an accessory.

11:18.673 --> 11:19.769
I can't make that deal.

11:20.246 --> 11:21.575
- She's not.
- Yeah.

11:21.715 --> 11:23.325
But she knows who did it.

11:23.989 --> 11:25.594
What if my client were able to prove

11:25.619 --> 11:27.869
that the murderer was
Sheriff Alex Romero?

11:29.619 --> 11:30.989
You can give us Romero?

11:34.561 --> 11:36.980
- Yeah.
- How?

11:38.480 --> 11:40.439
My client is willing to wear a wire.

11:40.682 --> 11:42.092
And why would he confess to her?

11:47.159 --> 11:48.696
Because we've had a long-standing

11:48.721 --> 11:50.471
romantic relationship.

12:05.936 --> 12:06.939
What's up?

12:06.940 --> 12:08.020
Thanks for meeting me here.

12:11.515 --> 12:14.099
Hi. Just a... just coffee, thanks.

12:14.350 --> 12:15.690
What's going on?

12:17.613 --> 12:18.943
Um...

12:22.257 --> 12:25.357
I don't think, uh... I
don't think Norman should be

12:25.382 --> 12:27.512
out of the mental institution.

12:31.645 --> 12:34.568
I think he might...
I think he's dangerous.

12:36.115 --> 12:38.900
And honestly, I'm... I'm afraid
to leave Norma alone with him.

12:41.784 --> 12:43.364
Okay, now, I'm... I'm only curious,

12:43.389 --> 12:47.100
but have you ever seen him
exhibit violent behavior?

12:53.770 --> 12:55.574
[sighs]

12:56.752 --> 12:58.449
Yes. Yeah, I have.

13:01.762 --> 13:03.418
I don't think he should be home either.

13:05.106 --> 13:07.610
Okay. Well, Norma can't, uh...

13:07.635 --> 13:09.099
she won't see it.

13:09.663 --> 13:11.543
You're, uh... you're
preaching to the choir.

13:12.770 --> 13:13.894
And I don't want to do this,

13:13.919 --> 13:17.144
but it might come down to us
having to have him committed.

13:20.328 --> 13:21.689
You mean behind Norma's back?

13:22.203 --> 13:23.898
Well, she's never gonna do it herself.

13:25.351 --> 13:26.769
Now, I can start legal proceedings

13:26.770 --> 13:28.439
to have him formally committed

13:28.635 --> 13:30.675
if I get the signatures
of two family members.

13:33.184 --> 13:34.524
You mean you and me.

13:36.309 --> 13:37.949
I don't know if I can do that to her.

13:38.314 --> 13:39.416
Well, I'm afraid something more's

13:39.441 --> 13:41.021
gonna happen if we don't, Dylan.

13:45.613 --> 13:48.729
Well, let me... let me
try and talk to her. Okay?

13:48.730 --> 13:51.769
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:13.315 --> 14:16.315
[washing machine whirring]

14:19.935 --> 14:22.935
[sustained beep]

14:29.235 --> 14:32.605
Oh, God. I didn't hear you come in.

14:35.235 --> 14:36.524
Where's Norman?

14:36.836 --> 14:38.506
He's down at the motel.

14:40.057 --> 14:41.057
What's wrong?

14:42.908 --> 14:44.321
I, um...

14:46.102 --> 14:47.552
I found this...

14:49.074 --> 14:51.323
In the pocket of your coat.

14:51.395 --> 14:53.419
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:53.444 --> 14:55.223
Emma was worried you
might be missing it.

14:56.231 --> 14:58.950
Yeah, I was missing it. What?

14:59.769 --> 15:01.308
This isn't your earring, Norma.

15:05.468 --> 15:06.330
This is Emma's mother's.

15:06.355 --> 15:08.103
She was wearing it in the hospital.

15:09.478 --> 15:10.864
Oh, yeah, yeah. Yeah, you're right.

15:10.889 --> 15:12.269
I would never wear that.

15:14.278 --> 15:16.605
- Can I have it?
- No, you can't.

15:20.033 --> 15:22.611
I don't know what
your problem is, Dylan.

15:22.636 --> 15:25.218
- Why did you have it, Norma?
- I just found it outside.

15:25.243 --> 15:26.623
I must have put it in my pocket.

15:29.312 --> 15:30.985
Then why were you
pretending like it was yours?

15:31.010 --> 15:32.296
It didn't seem worth explaining.

15:32.321 --> 15:34.401
Why are you making such
a big deal out of it?

15:39.326 --> 15:40.536
You need to listen to me, Norma.

15:40.561 --> 15:42.135
You're just talking a bunch of nonsense.

15:42.160 --> 15:44.199
I don't need to hear it.
I have enough going on.

15:45.116 --> 15:46.324
It's just a stupid earring.

15:46.325 --> 15:47.665
It doesn't mean anything.

15:49.731 --> 15:51.073
Then why were you keeping it?

15:51.775 --> 15:52.681
Stop hiding, Norma!

15:52.706 --> 15:54.335
I'm not hiding! What is wrong with you?

15:54.360 --> 15:55.661
Why did you have that
earring in your pocket?

15:55.686 --> 15:57.555
- I told you why!
- Stop lying to me!

15:57.580 --> 15:58.674
What do you want from me, Dylan?

15:58.699 --> 16:00.058
I want you to face the truth that's...

16:00.125 --> 16:01.411
It's right in front of us!

16:01.436 --> 16:03.356
- Norman is sick!
- He's seeing a doctor!

16:03.381 --> 16:04.670
- He's seeing a doctor...
- No! He shouldn't be...

16:04.694 --> 16:05.744
- three times a week!
- out of the institution!

16:05.745 --> 16:06.488
He's dangerous!

16:06.513 --> 16:08.117
- You don't know that!
- I know enough!

16:08.142 --> 16:09.824
Why do you keep doing this?

16:09.849 --> 16:11.909
Because I'm afraid of
what's gonna happen,

16:11.934 --> 16:12.840
of what's already happened.

16:12.865 --> 16:14.864
Stop being dramatic!

16:15.020 --> 16:16.849
You're just inventing all of this.

16:16.874 --> 16:19.159
You're making shit up
because you're jealous of him!

16:19.358 --> 16:20.994
You always have been!

16:20.995 --> 16:23.994
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:28.280 --> 16:29.686
[sighs] I'm sorry.

16:29.799 --> 16:31.548
It's not just me.

16:33.389 --> 16:35.589
Romero thinks the same, that
Norman should be committed.

16:38.735 --> 16:40.926
Dylan, wait. Wait!

16:41.285 --> 16:44.454
How do you know how he
feels? How do you know that?

16:44.670 --> 16:46.244
Because he told me.

16:46.245 --> 16:48.646
Okay? We talked. He...
he's worried just like I am.

16:49.021 --> 16:50.466
He thinks that when it comes to Norman,

16:50.491 --> 16:51.560
you can't see clearly.

16:52.116 --> 16:53.139
What?

16:53.193 --> 16:56.075
You're... you're so blind to
the... and you're trying so hard

16:56.100 --> 16:58.704
to protect him that you can't
see what's right around you!

16:58.893 --> 17:01.244
So the two of you are getting
together behind my back?

17:03.159 --> 17:04.584
Why? What's he gonna do about it?

17:07.026 --> 17:09.034
What... what... does
he want to commit Norman

17:09.059 --> 17:10.175
without telling me?

17:10.201 --> 17:11.769
- You should ask him.
- Dylan, tell me.

17:11.794 --> 17:13.087
Just... just talk to him, okay? Leave...

17:13.112 --> 17:14.559
Dylan, I'm your mother!

17:14.584 --> 17:16.560
You've never been a real mother to me!

17:19.204 --> 17:20.914
Never!

17:20.915 --> 17:22.624
Look, I... I have tried, okay?

17:22.625 --> 17:25.385
And I... I know that you've tried, too,

17:25.410 --> 17:29.414
and I... I can't do...
I can't do this anymore.

17:34.286 --> 17:35.826
I'm done, Norma.

17:37.954 --> 17:39.084
Dylan.

17:41.747 --> 17:43.836
Please give me the earring, please.

17:49.705 --> 17:51.334
[door closes]

17:54.057 --> 17:55.306
[door closes]

17:58.529 --> 18:01.608
<i>Dylan! Dylan, come back here!</i>

18:01.633 --> 18:02.744
Dylan?

18:03.189 --> 18:05.584
What... what's happening?
What's going on?

18:05.833 --> 18:07.832
What... what...

18:08.523 --> 18:09.591
Dylan!

18:12.129 --> 18:13.933
Norman, you're not well.

18:14.706 --> 18:16.389
You need to check yourself
back into Pineview.

18:16.414 --> 18:18.584
Please. Mom's never gonna do it for you.

18:18.828 --> 18:20.422
You have to do it for yourself.

18:20.813 --> 18:22.244
What are you talking about?

18:22.729 --> 18:24.479
Don't say anything to him.

18:34.632 --> 18:35.890
Good-bye, Norman.

18:35.915 --> 18:38.914
<i>[soft music]</i>

18:40.443 --> 18:41.954
Dylan.

18:42.431 --> 18:43.641
Dylan, what's going on?

18:43.666 --> 18:45.335
What's happening?

18:48.463 --> 18:49.706
Mother?

19:17.413 --> 19:20.083
[dishes rattling]

19:25.990 --> 19:27.330
Mother?

19:29.495 --> 19:32.495
What just happened? Tell me.

19:37.809 --> 19:40.349
Dylan doesn't think
that you should be home.

19:41.472 --> 19:42.472
Why?

19:48.357 --> 19:51.147
'Cause everyone thinks they
know more about you than I do.

19:58.385 --> 19:59.830
They're wrong.

20:01.576 --> 20:02.705
Everyone?

20:06.046 --> 20:07.426
Does Alex think this too?

20:09.389 --> 20:11.843
Yeah. I'll handle it.

20:15.054 --> 20:16.992
I have to go. I'm gonna to talk to Alex.

20:17.746 --> 20:18.832
Okay.

20:19.237 --> 20:21.285
You stay here until I
get back, though, okay?

20:21.310 --> 20:22.690
- Okay.
- Okay.

20:26.389 --> 20:27.849
Mother?

20:30.849 --> 20:32.638
I could get those
Christmas tree lights out,

20:32.639 --> 20:35.059
and we could both
start on that tomorrow.

20:37.810 --> 20:40.268
Yes, honey. I would love that.

20:40.269 --> 20:41.774
<i>[tender music]</i>

20:41.799 --> 20:43.128
I love you, Mother.

20:46.551 --> 20:47.668
I love you.

21:04.812 --> 21:05.856
Hey.

21:11.080 --> 21:14.034
I thought you were going
to, uh... to Indianapolis.

21:14.718 --> 21:17.979
Meh. I realized it was
foolish for me to try and run.

21:21.153 --> 21:23.112
So what now?

21:23.137 --> 21:25.506
Well, now I'm gonna eat my lunch

21:25.531 --> 21:28.611
and then get back to the bank.

21:33.139 --> 21:36.809
Do you remember when,
um... when we first met?

21:40.120 --> 21:41.728
It was at Bob's.

21:41.729 --> 21:42.808
Yeah, I remember.

21:42.809 --> 21:45.386
[chuckles] I hope you do.

21:46.045 --> 21:48.334
Afterwards we, uh... we
went back to my place,

21:48.359 --> 21:50.858
and I don't think we
got any sleep at all.

21:50.883 --> 21:51.882
You do remember that part, don't you?

21:51.889 --> 21:53.809
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

21:59.408 --> 22:03.495
There is one thing that
I never quite understood:

22:03.520 --> 22:07.899
how you and Bob were
friends in the first place.

22:07.939 --> 22:09.205
I mean, you knew what he was doing,

22:09.230 --> 22:11.612
that he was in the drug trade,

22:11.637 --> 22:13.346
and you were the
sheriff, but that didn't,

22:13.371 --> 22:16.410
like, really matter, so I never
quite understood that part,

22:16.435 --> 22:20.185
how that worked, your... your morality.

22:24.325 --> 22:25.478
Bob Paris was in the drug trade?

22:25.479 --> 22:27.006
I didn't... I didn't know that.

22:27.031 --> 22:31.045
[scoffs] Was it because
you two were friends

22:31.070 --> 22:32.762
from when you were kids?

22:32.787 --> 22:34.328
But apparently that didn't really matter

22:34.353 --> 22:35.943
when you put a bullet in his head.

22:37.762 --> 22:39.842
Why did you do it, Alex?

22:42.676 --> 22:44.598
So how did it go down?

22:44.599 --> 22:46.889
Where'd the DEA catch you? Was it here?

22:54.537 --> 22:56.308
Where's the mic?

22:56.748 --> 22:58.101
I just want to make sure I'm heard.

22:58.126 --> 22:59.666
Where is it?

23:04.333 --> 23:05.873
All right, come here.

23:07.955 --> 23:11.574
Uh, this is... this is to all
my friends over at the DEA.

23:11.856 --> 23:13.558
I've done nothing but be helpful to you,

23:13.692 --> 23:16.317
and it's 'cause of me that
you made dozens of arrests,

23:16.342 --> 23:18.558
and you shut down the
drug business in this town,

23:18.748 --> 23:20.478
and now you want to come after me?

23:20.479 --> 23:22.808
Well, you can all go to hell. All right?

23:23.019 --> 23:24.559
Sorry I couldn't be of more help.

23:39.577 --> 23:40.472
Your wife's here.

23:40.497 --> 23:42.377
She's in your office.

23:47.059 --> 23:48.889
- Hey.
- How dare you.

23:52.981 --> 23:54.598
- What?
- How dare you go

23:54.599 --> 23:56.173
behind my back to my own son

23:56.198 --> 23:57.806
to try and get Norman
taken away from me?

23:57.831 --> 23:58.981
Who the hell do you think you are?

23:59.006 --> 24:00.728
Someone who loves you
and is worried about you.

24:00.729 --> 24:02.164
- And Norman.
- That's nice

24:02.189 --> 24:03.954
that that's how you
frame it in your head,

24:03.979 --> 24:05.153
but how it looks from here

24:05.178 --> 24:07.907
is that you are an incredibly
presumptuous and arrogant man

24:07.932 --> 24:09.636
who thinks he knows what's
best for me and my son.

24:09.661 --> 24:11.207
Wow. I'm sorry you see it that way.

24:11.232 --> 24:13.174
No one who loves me
could ever do this to me.

24:13.199 --> 24:14.916
No. That's where you're
wrong. He's dangerous.

24:14.941 --> 24:15.766
He's my son!

24:15.791 --> 24:17.660
You don't think I would
know if he was dangerous?

24:17.685 --> 24:19.801
He had an axe in his hand,
and he wanted to kill me!

24:19.826 --> 24:21.475
Yeah, well, are you dead?

24:22.139 --> 24:24.195
The point is, he didn't! He was angry!

24:24.220 --> 24:25.579
He took it out on the shed

24:25.604 --> 24:26.934
and on my door.

24:32.168 --> 24:35.490
You know, [sigh] we were happy

24:35.515 --> 24:38.728
when we were in a bubble,
but life isn't a bubble.

24:39.093 --> 24:41.858
You know, the second that
a little reality crept in,

24:41.883 --> 24:42.821
that was it for you.

24:42.846 --> 24:44.938
Bam. So much for the stupid bubble.

24:44.939 --> 24:46.721
You can spin it however you want, Norma.

24:46.746 --> 24:47.534
It doesn't make it the truth.

24:47.559 --> 24:49.657
You just... you can't see clearly

24:49.682 --> 24:50.745
here 'cause this is about Norman.

24:50.770 --> 24:52.228
Yeah, because he's my son!

24:52.325 --> 24:53.682
You're gonna plant
yourself on the mountain

24:53.707 --> 24:55.226
like you're God and tell me

24:55.251 --> 24:57.638
how things work with my son?

24:57.765 --> 25:00.993
Wrong. You crossed over a line,
and you are never crossing back.

25:01.018 --> 25:02.093
I will never trust you again.

25:02.118 --> 25:03.002
No, you left me no choice.

25:03.027 --> 25:04.284
And you left me none.

25:04.309 --> 25:07.308
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:50.889 --> 25:53.888
<i>[ominous music]</i>

27:52.592 --> 27:55.592
[wind whistling]

28:00.722 --> 28:01.762
[dirt thumps]

28:06.682 --> 28:09.682
[water running]

28:20.302 --> 28:22.512
[door creaks open]

28:38.776 --> 28:40.276
Where have you been, Mother?

28:42.889 --> 28:44.389
I was worried about you.

28:46.776 --> 28:48.251
Just, um...

28:48.276 --> 28:50.936
What? What happened?

28:57.208 --> 28:58.704
You were right.

29:00.106 --> 29:02.316
It's not gonna work with Alex and me.

29:23.412 --> 29:24.912
I'm sorry, Mother.

29:26.606 --> 29:28.605
It's okay.

29:28.606 --> 29:30.566
Another day, another dollar, whatever.

29:36.622 --> 29:38.396
Leftovers okay, honey?

29:45.276 --> 29:48.316
[ragged breathing]

29:55.776 --> 29:58.775
[crying]

29:58.776 --> 30:01.775
<i>[emotional music]</i>

30:01.776 --> 30:04.775
[sobbing]

30:11.355 --> 30:13.354
I'm so sorry, Mother.

31:49.390 --> 31:50.769
I just came to say good night.

31:53.592 --> 31:55.091
Come in, honey.

32:04.436 --> 32:05.686
[sighs]

32:07.146 --> 32:10.356
[sniffles]

32:28.724 --> 32:30.804
I think maybe we should
move somewhere else.

32:36.121 --> 32:37.541
So much has happened here.

32:39.370 --> 32:41.395
We have tried our best, Mother.

32:41.396 --> 32:42.871
We really have.

32:43.293 --> 32:46.266
I know we love this old house,
but I don't think you can say

32:46.291 --> 32:47.961
it's been a good place for us.

32:48.657 --> 32:51.145
I don't know. In some ways it has.

32:51.146 --> 32:53.526
Well, why are we both
broken right now, Mother?

32:56.436 --> 32:58.485
Life is hard,

32:58.486 --> 33:02.605
but we still have each other,

33:02.606 --> 33:05.525
and we will always have each other,

33:05.526 --> 33:07.485
and nothing will ever change that,

33:07.486 --> 33:08.856
and that's everything.

33:18.301 --> 33:21.685
Do you remember when
you said you wanted to go

33:21.686 --> 33:23.356
and move to Oahu?

33:25.030 --> 33:29.533
That it was safer
because it was an island?

33:29.558 --> 33:32.275
[laughs] I do.

33:32.276 --> 33:33.899
I remember.

33:33.924 --> 33:35.435
Then why don't we go there?

33:35.436 --> 33:37.225
[laughs]

33:37.250 --> 33:40.443
- Because we have no money.
- Well, so we save up.

33:40.468 --> 33:41.935
We sell what we can sell.

33:41.936 --> 33:45.185
The furniture in this place
must be worth something.

33:45.186 --> 33:47.277
We just walk away from the house.

33:47.302 --> 33:48.895
We let the bank have it.

33:48.982 --> 33:50.912
We buy two tickets to Oahu.

33:51.451 --> 33:53.016
We get jobs there.

33:53.486 --> 33:55.145
We get a little apartment

33:55.146 --> 33:58.105
and walk on down to the beach every day

33:58.319 --> 33:59.605
and live on macadamia nuts.

33:59.606 --> 34:00.815
[laughs]

34:00.816 --> 34:04.493
[both laughing]

34:04.518 --> 34:07.302
You always loved new beginnings, Mother.

34:07.327 --> 34:09.282
Fresh starts.

34:09.962 --> 34:12.868
I don't think I can start over, Norman.

34:12.893 --> 34:14.650
I think you can, Mother.

34:15.626 --> 34:16.895
You will.

34:17.525 --> 34:19.121
We'll just do it together.

34:19.800 --> 34:23.516
